AN  - 2024746803
T1  - The Diagnostics and Treatment of Recurrent Pregnancy Loss
A1  - Tomkiewicz J.
A1  - Darmochwal-Kolarz D. 
AO  - Tomkiewicz, Julia; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1443-1229
Y1  - 2023//
N2  - Recurrent pregnancy loss is a common problem in the reproductive age population of women. It can be caused by many different conditions. This problem is addressed in international guidelines that take a slightly different approach to its diagnosis and treatment. The guidelines used in this review mainly use the guidelines of the Royal College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (RCOG), American Society of Reproductive Medicine (ASRM) and European Society of Human Reproduction and Embryology (ESHRE). This review shows how much the approach to miscarriages has changed and how much more needs to be explored and refined. The review also addresses the topic of unexplained pregnancy loss, which continues to be a challenge for clinicians.Copyright © 2023 by the authors.
