144. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2026084208
T1  - Ovulation induction in polycystic ovarian syndrome: A review to contemporary approaches
A1  - Chouhan P.
A1  - Garg A.K. 
Y1  - 2023//
N2  - Polycystic ovarian syndrome (PCOS) is an endocrine condition that impacts women's reproductive capabilities and causes them to be infertile. Anovulation is the most common cause of PCOS infertility, although it is not alone. The ongoing hormonal imbalance causes complications such as cysts and an abnormal menstrual cycle, leading to infertility. A few of the reasons for PCOS have been discovered as several potential genes. PCOS is a heterogeneous syndrome that primarily affects women between the ages of 18 and 44 years. There are several methods of ovulation induction (OI) that can be made to make females fertile. Recent research has been conducted on OI using mediation, surgery, lifestyle changes, symptom, and treatment. On the other hand, each of these methods was limited to single or single-pathway research. Because PCOS is complex involving a gene regulatory milieu, it may be prone to the transient, self-limiting occurrence of endometrial receptivity. To induce ovulation in PCOS patients, genomic-based assessment is needed for therapeutic purposes.Copyright © 2023 Journal of Medical Society.
