553. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 621478153
T1  - Insulin resistance-pathway from impaired glucose tolerance to diabetes and metabolic syndrome
T3  - Insulin Resistance Symposium 2017. Izmir Turkey.
A1  - Oguz A. 
Y1  - 2017//
N2  - Metabolic syndrome is a modern age disease characterized with hyperglycemia, dyslipidemia, hypertension and abdominal obesity. Copresence of various risk factors which have a role in development of cardiovascular diseases and type 2 diabetes and considered to be sharing a common etiopathogenesis is defined as metabolic syndrome. In this picture insulin resistance has a primary role. Insulin sensitivity is a marker of response to glucose uptake of various tissues which are insulin dependent particularly skeletal muscle and it also shows ability to suppress gluconeogenesis in liver and lipolysis in adipose tissue. The main pathology in metabolic syndrome is post receptor insulin resistance. Adipose tissue and hormones secreted from adipose tissue, disorders of hypothalamus-pituitary-adrenal gland axis, advanced age, genetic and environmental causes are among other factors which play a role in development of metabolic syndrome. Insulin resistance is the beginning of the road to type 2 diabetes. It has a very different presentation than type 1 diabetes. In type 2 diabetes insulin resistance plays the key role, not insulin deficiency and it is closely related to increased adipose tissue /lipid metabolism. In fact, in recent guidelines type 2 diabetes is defined as an element of metabolic syndrome. Non-alcoholic steatohepatitis, polycystic ovary syndrome, sleep apnea syndrome, cholelithiasis, gastroesophageal reflux, depression and asthma are disorders associated with metabolic syndrome. Primary approach for metabolic syndrome is adjustment of life style. Weight loss with an appropriate diet and exercise program would cause an ameliorating effect for all the disorders seen in metabolic syndrome.
