653. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 43623700
ID  - 16647666 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16647666]
T1  - Metabolic Syndrome: Screening, Diagnosis, and Management
A1  - Miller E.L.
A1  - Mitchell A. 
Y1  - 2006//
N2  - Metabolic syndrome, a growing issue in women's health, is a cluster of health findings that increase the risk of cardiovascular events. The prevalence of metabolic syndrome is higher in women and is linked to several conditions unique to women's health, including polycystic ovary syndrome, gestational diabetes, pregnancy-induced hypertension, and female sexual dysfunction. Risk factors, screening strategies, and therapeutic management of metabolic syndrome in women are discussed. © 2006 American College of Nurse-Midwives.
